-v : Verbose (basic debug information)
-vv : More verbose (detailed debug information)
-vvv : Even more verbose (connection details)
-vvvv : Debug level (includes SSH connection details)
-vvvvv : Extended debug level (includes more details, useful for troubleshooting deep issues)

 run playbook : ansible-playbook -i hosts.ini playbook.yml   

 #note  -i this mean inventry file if you not mention -i in your command ansible will take inventry file as /etc/ansible/hosts this location

 debug command : ansible-playbook -i playbook.yml -v



sysntax check command : ansible-playbook --syntax-check playbook.yml



list task: ansible-playbook --list-task playbook.yml


dry run : ansible-playbook -i .ini playbook.yml --check




ansible-inventory Command
